Shares rose around 0.5 per cent on a day when the wider FTSE 100 Index headed downwards in the wake of overnight gloom on world markets.

The April 2010 spill occurred after 
BP's Macondo well blew out, causing the Deepwater Horizon drilling rig 
to explode, killing 11 workers.

Millions of gallons of oil spewed into the Gulf, with crude soiling shoreline and beaches from Louisiana to Florida.

 

